1978.   I live in Geneva and I'm studying engineering.  I started computing
with an old MSX-2 and with some old PC's.  When I was about 12 years old, I
bought an Amiga 500 and I discovered how great this machine was.  Now, I've
got  an  expanded CDł˛.  I'll probably set up a BBS named Strike BBS (it is
